SIMPLE: cavernous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cavernous
<hw>Cav"ern*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cavernosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>caverneux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Full of caverns; resembling a cavern or large cavity;
hollow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Filled with small cavities or cells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having a sound caused by a cavity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cavernous body</b></col>, <cd>a body of erectile tissue
with large interspaces which may be distended with blood, as in the
penis or clitoris.</cd> -- <col><b>Cavernous respiration</b></col>,
<cd>a peculiar respiratory sound andible on auscultation, when the
bronchial tubes communicate with morbid cavities in the
lungs.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cavernulous</ent>⟦br⟧
